          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch modifies the Btrfs file system's readahead behavior to release extent locks per folio, rather than holding them for the entire range. This change is intended to prevent a race condition between readahead and direct IO writes, which can cause tasks to hang on the extent lock. The problem arises when readahead fails due to memory allocation issues, leaving pages in an inconsistent state and causing subsequent reads to block on the extent lock. By releasing locks per folio, the patch aims to alleviate this issue and reduce stress on the system.",
